# Shruti Ada Portfolio — Project Context

## Tech Stack
- **Astro 5** static site generator
- **Tailwind CSS 3** for styling (config in `tailwind.config.mjs`)
- Custom fonts: **Sugarpie** (hand-drawn body, 24–36px), **NewUnderground** (bold display headings, 57–64px)
- Crumpled paper background texture

## Design System
- Crumpled paper texture backgrounds (applied via `global.css`)
- Black text on paper texture — no color palette needed
- Hand-drawn doodle characters placed at specific positions on each page
- Fonts convey the entire personality — Sugarpie for body, NewUnderground for headings

## Architecture
- Multi-page portfolio with dedicated routes (not single-page anchors)
- Header nav links to `/illustrations`, `/works`, `/services`, `/about`
- Portfolio data lives in `src/data/portfolio.ts` — illustrations and works arrays
- Dynamic routes: `src/pages/illustrations/[slug].astro` and `src/pages/works/[slug].astro`
- Gallery pages: `src/pages/illustrations.astro` and `src/pages/works.astro`
- All artwork images in `public/images/portfolio/`
- Works project images in `public/images/works/[project-slug]/`
- Doodle images in `public/images/doodles/`

## Figma Conversion — Critical Rules

### Sizing: Always Use `vw` Units
- **NEVER use fixed `px` values** for font-size, padding, margin, width, or height
- Convert Figma px to vw: `px / 1365 * 100 = vw` (frame width is 1365px)
- Common conversions: 64px = 4.6886vw, 57px = 4.1758vw, 32px = 2.3443vw, 24px = 1.7582vw, 36px = 2.6374vw
- This ensures proportional scaling at any viewport width

### Doodle Images: Render from Figma API
- **NEVER guess CSS transforms** (rotate, scaleX, scaleY) for doodle orientation
- Instead, render the specific Figma node as a PNG using the Figma render API (`/v1/images/{file}?ids=NODE_ID&format=png&scale=2`)
- This bakes in all Figma transforms (rotation, flip) into the image itself
- Save pre-rendered doodles to `public/images/doodles/`
- If a doodle has excessive transparent padding, crop it programmatically (Python Pillow)

### Text: Extract Exact Styles from Figma
- Use `node.style.fontFamily`, `fontSize`, `fontWeight`, `textAlignHorizontal` from Figma API
- Never guess font sizes — always derive from the cached Figma data in `scripts/figma-cache/all-pages.json`
- Text should not have fixed `width` that causes premature wrapping — let it flow naturally

### Layout Positioning
- Use `position: absolute` with vw-based `left`/`top`/`right` for doodles and overlapping elements
- Use CSS `columns` for masonry grids (no JS needed)
- Marquee animations use `@keyframes` with `translateX(-50%)` and duplicated content for seamless loop
- Marquee speed: currently 160s for gallery/detail pages, 180s for landing page

### Figma Data Access
- Cached Figma API data: `scripts/figma-cache/all-pages.json`
- Contains all pages: landing (0:1), gallery (2:8), individual view (3:47), case study (3:76), services (3:132), about (4:183)
- Each node has `absoluteBoundingBox` (x, y, width, height), `style` (fonts), `fills` (imageRef)
- Figma file key: `fzcw08xG5ByHbIZnnxR2GY`
- Figma token: stored in scripts, use for API calls

## Works Data Model
Works use a flexible `sections` array — each section has a `type` ("full-width", "marquee", "masonry"), optional `label`, and `images` array. This allows each project to define its own unique layout.

## Key Patterns
- Header component in `src/components/Header.astro` — shared across all pages
- Base layout in `src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro` — includes header, lightbox, mobile menu
- Marquee: duplicate the image set for seamless infinite scroll, pause on hover
- CTA sections: "Like what you see?" + doodles pattern reused on illustration and works detail pages
- All new images go in `public/images/` (referenced as `/images/...`)
- Navigation uses proper page routes, not anchor links

## When Editing
- Keep the hand-drawn, playful aesthetic consistent
- All values in `vw` — never introduce fixed `px` sizing
- When adding doodles, always render from Figma API (don't apply CSS transforms)
- Test responsiveness by resizing viewport — everything should scale proportionally
- Alternating left/right alignment pattern used on services page
